@startuml recall-consolidate-delta-compaction
' Consolidation under RB_DELTA_TIER: the MINOR fold (cheap, every recall flush)
' and the MAJOR compaction (only at RB_MAX_DELTAS). Contrast with the single-shard
' full rewrite in recall-consolidate-consolidation.puml, which rebuilt the WHOLE
' shard on EVERY flush -- the cause of the recall-growth "cliff" under sustained
' writes. Here a flush is O(new rows); the generation is rebuilt only once every
' RB_MAX_DELTAS folds.

title Delta-tier consolidation: cheap minor fold + periodic major compaction (RB_DELTA_TIER on)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam NoteFontSize 10
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

participant "index_builder\n(_run_consolidate_locked)" as builder
database "Recall\n(pgvector)" as recall
database "shard_catalog\n(generations, frontier)" as catalog
database "S3 shards\n(base + deltas + quantizer)" as s3

== MINOR FOLD -- every recall flush (cap RB_RECALL_MAX_ROWS or idle RB_RECALL_IDLE_S) ==

builder -> catalog : live_generation(tenant,dataset)\n-> base + live deltas + frontier
activate builder
builder -> recall : snapshot recall rows WHERE lsn > frontier\n(ONLY the band above the frontier -- O(new rows))
builder -> s3 : load quantizer-vG (frozen) -> clone trained-empty\n-> bare IVFFlat, add_with_ids(new rows) -> delta blob
builder -> catalog : add_shard(level=1, parent=base, quantizer_version=G,\ncovered_lsn_lo=frontier+1, covered_lsn_hi=N,\ntombstone_int_ids=deleted ids above frontier)
note right of catalog
  Commit-before-trim (I2). The frontier advances by the new
  contiguous band; recall rows <= new frontier become eligible
  for the grace-bounded trim (kept while < 2 generations old).
end note
deactivate builder

alt live deltas < RB_MAX_DELTAS (8)
  builder -> builder : done -- fan-out still bounded, return
else live deltas reach RB_MAX_DELTAS  (_maybe_major_compaction)
  == MAJOR COMPACTION ==
  builder -> s3 : reconstruct deduped survivors across base + deltas\n(newest-occurrence-wins; drop tombstoned ids)
  activate builder
  builder -> s3 : build a FRESH base under a CLONED quantizer-vG\n(same version, NO retrain) -- the only O(generation) step
  builder -> catalog : add_shard(new base, level=0) -> TRANSACTIONAL cutover\n(the new generation becomes live atomically)
  builder -> catalog : grace sweep -- superseded_shards drops generations\n> 2 old (membership-based, not list-position)
  note right of builder #FBE9E9
    Heaviest op: peak RSS ~ generation size (~3.9 GB at 1M / dim-128),
    so it must run on a higher-memory lane. Phase-2: stream the
    reconstruct under an explicit RSS budget.
  end note
  deactivate builder
end

@enduml
